WEBVTT

00:00.834 --> 00:02.449
If I don't work,
we'll have to steal.

00:02.586 --> 00:03.917
We both know
that's not why you do it.

00:04.046 --> 00:05.206
I'm not going to stop.

00:05.339 --> 00:06.829
-Nor will I.
-V: What are you doing?

00:06.965 --> 00:08.216
Trying to give you a body.

00:08.342 --> 00:10.173
Uploading you
into a special synthetic.

00:10.302 --> 00:12.588
I understand that things
don't make sense yet.

00:12.721 --> 00:14.086
Because you have to grow.

00:14.223 --> 00:16.179
KAREN: I spoke to the super
this morning.

00:16.308 --> 00:18.469
-I said I'd start back Monday.
-You sure you're ready?

00:18.602 --> 00:19.591
I'll be fine.

00:19.728 --> 00:20.888
MATTIE: I'm looking for
an old D-series.

00:21.021 --> 00:22.932
Might have been brought in
a few months ago.

00:23.065 --> 00:24.896
The code they made
makes synths conscious.

00:25.025 --> 00:26.606
So I'm gonna find out
how this works,

00:26.735 --> 00:29.898
use it to make him conscious,
and find out anything he knows.

00:30.030 --> 00:32.737
You told me I should face
justice for killing that man.

00:32.866 --> 00:35.278
But I want to be tried
as a human would be.

00:35.410 --> 00:36.274
If you'll help me.

00:36.411 --> 00:39.369
You hand it over to have an
independent expert assessment.

00:39.498 --> 00:41.784
If she proves she's conscious,
does she get her trial?

00:41.917 --> 00:43.077
-Mm-hmm.
-And if she fails?

00:43.210 --> 00:45.201
We terminate it.

00:48.757 --> 00:51.669
[ Mid-tempo music plays]

01:08.485 --> 01:10.567
[ Music continues]

01:36.054 --> 01:37.794
FEMALE VOICE:
Going up.

01:42.144 --> 01:44.556
[ Monitor beeping]

01:55.532 --> 01:57.113
Good morning, Dr. Morrow.

01:57.242 --> 01:58.857
Leave us.

02:07.294 --> 02:09.376
Hello, baby.

02:11.632 --> 02:13.543
Hello.

03:02.766 --> 03:05.098
[ Monitor beeping]

03:16.613 --> 03:18.649
I said leave us.

03:28.291 --> 03:30.452
We have to talk.

03:32.421 --> 03:35.003
It's been three years, Athena.

03:35.132 --> 03:37.043
We have to move on.

03:38.969 --> 03:40.584
I miss her.

03:41.555 --> 03:43.136
Every day.

03:43.265 --> 03:45.506
-I think about her, and --
-Do you really?

03:46.143 --> 03:47.679
How can you say that?

03:50.105 --> 03:52.562
There's nothing anyone can do.

03:52.691 --> 03:55.307
That's...
That's not our daughter.

03:55.444 --> 03:56.354
That's not Ginny.

03:56.486 --> 03:58.863
[Sighs]

03:58.989 --> 04:00.445
I'm sorry, but I -- | just...

04:03.368 --> 04:05.154
| just can't do this anymore.

04:05.287 --> 04:07.073
Can't do what?

04:07.664 --> 04:10.326
We need to start listening to
what the doctors are telling us.

04:12.419 --> 04:14.660
l have the documents.
All you have to do is agree.

04:14.796 --> 04:16.878
[Sighs]

04:18.508 --> 04:20.590
l'm, uh, I'm going to England.

04:20.719 --> 04:22.459
Athena, please.

04:22.596 --> 04:24.678
We'll talk when | get back.

04:33.815 --> 04:37.148
If I ever murder someone, can I
have you as my defense lawyer?

04:37.277 --> 04:40.064
Well, I might not be one
after this.

04:40.197 --> 04:41.687
They said I can work
on Niska's case,

04:41.823 --> 04:44.565
but if we don't win,
they deny any involvement.

04:45.202 --> 04:46.942
No pressure, then.

04:48.121 --> 04:49.657
LAURA: How are you feeling
about going back?

04:49.790 --> 04:52.827
Well, I never thought
I'd be working on the floor,

04:52.959 --> 04:54.244
but it's a job, isn't it?

04:56.004 --> 04:58.711
At least they can't sack me
for a back-to-work scheme.

04:58.840 --> 05:00.171
I'll have to go.

05:00.300 --> 05:02.256
Are you sure you're okay
to take the kids?

05:02.385 --> 05:06.503
Yeah. Course. Don't have to
be there till 9:30.

05:06.640 --> 05:08.005
Good luck.

05:08.141 --> 05:11.554
Yeah. Well, I'd say the same
to you, but you won't need it.

05:11.686 --> 05:13.301
Give 'em hell.

05:17.400 --> 05:19.732
[ Rapid beeping]

05:21.988 --> 05:23.319
[Sighs]

05:23.448 --> 05:24.688
I'm gonna be totally honest.

05:24.825 --> 05:26.235
You're still not looking
that great.

05:32.040 --> 05:34.531
[ Mid-tempo music plays]

06:05.824 --> 06:07.564
Okay.

06:09.286 --> 06:11.368
[ Computer beeps]

06:19.546 --> 06:21.832
[ Beeping ]

06:32.475 --> 06:35.933
[ Tone plays ]

06:43.320 --> 06:45.060
[Beep]

06:47.657 --> 06:49.613
Apricot.

06:50.160 --> 06:54.153
Cot -- Cot -- Cot.

06:54.289 --> 06:57.531
Cot -- Apri. . .cot.

06:57.667 --> 06:59.043
Co-- A-Apricot.

06:59.169 --> 07:01.660
[ Footsteps approaching ]

07:13.767 --> 07:14.847
Are you ready?

07:16.686 --> 07:18.347
I think so.

07:18.480 --> 07:21.062
[ lndistinct conversations]

07:40.669 --> 07:42.751
[ Beeping ]

07:57.435 --> 08:00.472
This chamber will measure
your reaction

08:00.605 --> 08:03.312
to different types of stimulus.

08:04.067 --> 08:06.183
None of it will hurt.

08:06.736 --> 08:08.818
The one thing I do know

08:08.947 --> 08:13.737
is you're gonna need to try
to open up.

08:13.868 --> 08:14.994
What does that mean?

08:15.120 --> 08:18.487
Show them how you feel,
that you can feel.

08:19.207 --> 08:21.448
Everything depends on that.

08:21.584 --> 08:23.666
[ Up-tempo music plays]

08:50.363 --> 08:51.944
Mia?

08:54.701 --> 08:57.363
Mia?
Are you all right?

09:06.379 --> 09:07.494
What's wrong?

09:07.630 --> 09:09.712
I care about someone.

09:11.217 --> 09:13.208
A human.

09:18.224 --> 09:20.761
He saw what I am...

09:21.811 --> 09:24.063
...and he told me to leave.

09:26.858 --> 09:29.645
But I can't stop thinking
about him.

09:29.778 --> 09:32.019
MAX: Maybe you should go back
and talk to him again.

09:32.155 --> 09:34.396
Maybe he was frightened.

09:35.325 --> 09:38.067
That's understandable.

09:55.553 --> 09:57.965
[Hinges squeak]

10:01.726 --> 10:03.762
Mia, we can feel.

10:04.604 --> 10:06.890
We were made to feel.

10:09.150 --> 10:10.435
We can't deny that.

10:10.568 --> 10:11.523
[ Door opens ]

10:11.653 --> 10:14.190
We need to get out now!

10:14.322 --> 10:16.404
[ Up-tempo music plays]

10:17.534 --> 10:19.399
He's gone.
He's escaped.

10:19.536 --> 10:20.696
I let him go.

10:20.829 --> 10:22.865
You -- What?

10:22.997 --> 10:24.533
Do you realize what you've done?

10:24.666 --> 10:26.452
You've put us all in danger!

10:26.584 --> 10:27.573
-But. ..
-What?

10:29.879 --> 10:30.994
Nothing.

10:32.632 --> 10:33.997
Come on.
We need to get out now.

10:34.134 --> 10:36.295
He'll lead them straight to us.

10:36.427 --> 10:38.509
[ Door opens ]

10:39.264 --> 10:40.595
Mia.

10:41.933 --> 10:43.844
Come on.

10:43.977 --> 10:45.433
I'm not coming.

10:47.772 --> 10:50.058
What are you talking about?
Of course you are.

10:50.859 --> 10:52.724
I want to stay here.

10:53.361 --> 10:54.692
You can't.
Why would you stay?

10:54.821 --> 10:57.062
She says she has feelings
for a human.

10:57.699 --> 10:59.030
A man.

10:59.659 --> 11:00.523
What?

11:00.660 --> 11:02.400
She's right.

11:03.413 --> 11:04.698
Who?

11:05.331 --> 11:07.788
The man you work for
at the cafÃ©.

11:07.917 --> 11:09.657
Mia, he -- he won't accept you.

11:09.794 --> 11:11.785
None of them c-can.

11:14.924 --> 11:16.630
l have to try.

11:18.595 --> 11:19.880
I want to.

11:20.680 --> 11:22.090
Well...

11:25.518 --> 11:28.635
You can't stay in this house.
It's not safe anymore.

11:29.522 --> 11:31.353
Okay.

11:31.983 --> 11:33.189
All right.

11:33.318 --> 11:35.479
Leo.

11:35.612 --> 11:36.897
Listen to Max.

11:50.585 --> 11:52.200
Bye, Maxie.

11:52.837 --> 11:54.418
I'll see you soon.

12:06.643 --> 12:09.100
How is it that you can have
feelings for a human?

12:10.563 --> 12:12.394
Some of them are worth it.

12:16.444 --> 12:19.527
What exactly
are you frightened of?

12:20.156 --> 12:22.317
You know what that
is capable of.

12:22.450 --> 12:24.736
Look, I know
what you're trying to do --

12:24.869 --> 12:26.780
establish human rights
by stealth.

12:28.539 --> 12:30.871
The horror, the monster.
Them and us. It's classic.

12:31.000 --> 12:32.251
All right.

12:32.377 --> 12:35.084
A 3% charge
is perfectly acceptable.

12:35.213 --> 12:38.046
This is an appliance we're
talking about with zero rights.

12:38.174 --> 12:38.959
At the moment.

12:39.092 --> 12:41.253
It's a machine
until proven otherwise.

12:41.386 --> 12:42.421
That's my decision.

12:42.553 --> 12:47.217
Now, you have the next 72 hours
to run the agreed tests.

12:47.350 --> 12:50.558
You will observe, question,
and assess this synthetic.

12:50.687 --> 12:52.268
Everything is to be recorded,

12:52.397 --> 12:55.013
and everything admissible
can be referenced by you both

12:55.149 --> 12:56.138
in your arguments.

12:56.276 --> 12:58.608
I will then make a judgment.

12:58.736 --> 13:01.603
lf consciousness is proven
to my satisfaction,

13:01.739 --> 13:04.071
the subject will stand trial
for the murder of Andrew Graham.

13:04.200 --> 13:06.441
If not, it will be disposed of
in the same way

13:06.577 --> 13:07.987
as any other
malfunctioning synthetic.

13:08.121 --> 13:09.486
Are we clear?

13:09.622 --> 13:10.452
Yes.

13:11.624 --> 13:13.956
ls your...client ready?

13:14.085 --> 13:16.747
[ Down-tempo music plays]

13:17.505 --> 13:19.166
She's ready.

13:26.180 --> 13:28.136
WOMAN ON P.A.:
Warehouse operative,

13:28.266 --> 13:31.474
your shift will begin
in three minutes.

13:31.602 --> 13:34.389
[ Mid-tempo music plays]

13:36.024 --> 13:38.106
[ Rattling ]

13:45.325 --> 13:46.735
[ Beeping ]

13:50.455 --> 13:54.243
Would Chris and Derek please
report to the main office?

13:55.335 --> 13:56.450
[ Door closes ]

13:56.586 --> 13:59.623
[ lndistinct conversations]

14:02.175 --> 14:04.461
Anyway.
Shall we?

14:08.306 --> 14:10.388
[ Mid-tempo music plays]

14:15.396 --> 14:18.888
[ Beeping ]

14:39.170 --> 14:40.956
Well?

14:41.089 --> 14:42.044
Nothing.

14:42.173 --> 14:43.458
Keep going.

14:43.591 --> 14:45.957
[ Music continues]

14:56.396 --> 14:58.637
[ lndistinct conversations]

15:19.377 --> 15:21.743
Hi.
You Renie?

15:27.343 --> 15:29.208
l'm Toby.

15:30.555 --> 15:33.046
We're, uh,
in some of the same classes.

15:33.724 --> 15:34.634
Hello, Toby.

15:34.767 --> 15:37.429
How can I be of assistance
to you?

15:38.896 --> 15:40.272
Oh, do you want some of mine?

15:41.357 --> 15:44.269
That won't be necessary,
thank you.

15:45.361 --> 15:48.228
[ lndistinct conversations,
laughter]

15:49.407 --> 15:51.568
How long you been doing
all this?

15:52.785 --> 15:56.073
Um...l think it's cool.

15:56.622 --> 15:57.327
I do.

15:57.457 --> 16:01.496
l was just...you know,
wondering.

16:02.170 --> 16:04.786
I'm afraid I don't understand
the question.

16:07.967 --> 16:10.253
Goodbye, Toby.

16:10.386 --> 16:12.342
And he crashes and burns
with a synthie!

16:12.472 --> 16:15.179
[ Laughter]

16:17.977 --> 16:20.263
[ lndistinct conversations]

16:27.028 --> 16:28.768
-Hey!
-He||o.

16:28.905 --> 16:30.441
Look who it is!

16:30.573 --> 16:31.562
How you doing?

16:31.699 --> 16:33.030
Fine!
Raring to go.

16:33.159 --> 16:34.319
How's everything with your,
uh...

16:34.452 --> 16:37.068
Dad. Yes.
Much better, thank you.

16:37.205 --> 16:40.242
It was touch-and-go for a while
but all okay now.

16:40.374 --> 16:42.501
That's really great.
Pub tonight?

16:42.627 --> 16:45.039
Definitely.
[ Chuckles ]

16:45.171 --> 16:46.911
Right.
Gather 'round, everyone.

16:47.048 --> 16:49.539
[ lndistinct conversations]

16:50.843 --> 16:52.003
Good to have you back,
D.|. Voss.

16:52.136 --> 16:53.296
Good to be back.

16:55.723 --> 16:56.883
PETE:
We're looking at an increase

16:57.016 --> 16:59.132
of so-called
"unusual malfunctions."

16:59.268 --> 17:02.601
15 reported last month
and another one this morning.

17:02.730 --> 17:04.812
Bike-courier synth cycled
off course

17:04.941 --> 17:07.148
and started going the wrong way
down a main road.

17:07.276 --> 17:08.812
This is the way
it seems to go --

17:08.945 --> 17:12.437
Primary user reports strange
behavior, synth goes AWOL.

17:12.573 --> 17:14.609
By the time we arrive,
the synth's gone

17:14.742 --> 17:16.698
and the owner changes
their story.

17:16.827 --> 17:18.408
We're thinking insurance scam.

17:18.538 --> 17:20.028
Should I get onto
this courier one?

17:20.164 --> 17:22.655
No. Don't worry. I'm on that.
What else?

17:22.792 --> 17:25.374
We're seeing supply-chain thefts
of specific parts.

17:25.503 --> 17:27.084
Interestingly,
never full synths.

17:27.213 --> 17:30.956
Karen, um, have a look at
the file and get up to speed.

17:31.092 --> 17:33.083
-KAREN: Of course.
-PETE: Thanks, everyone.

17:37.515 --> 17:39.096
You okay?

17:39.225 --> 17:41.056
I'm fine.
Stop worrying.

17:41.185 --> 17:44.177
Obviously, it's a bit more
than an insurance scam.

17:44.313 --> 17:46.474
What do you think about getting
out and feeling a few collars?

17:46.607 --> 17:47.983
-The courier?
-No.

17:48.109 --> 17:50.566
Remember that head cracker l was
banging on about pricy synths?

17:50.695 --> 17:52.811
-Yeah.
-Let's pay him a visit.

17:52.947 --> 17:55.313
[ Birds crying, waves breaking ]

17:55.449 --> 17:57.986
[ Down-tempo music plays]

18:19.348 --> 18:22.260
[ Lock clicks, keys jingle ]

18:28.482 --> 18:30.473
What are you doing here?

18:33.279 --> 18:35.361
I need to talk to you.

18:35.948 --> 18:37.279
Please.

18:43.831 --> 18:44.946
ED:
Well?

18:45.082 --> 18:47.118
I need to know I can trust you.

18:47.251 --> 18:50.118
[ Exhales sharply]

18:50.254 --> 18:52.119
I'm serious.

18:53.382 --> 18:55.418
Being this...

18:56.844 --> 18:58.550
...being me...

19:00.306 --> 19:02.388
...is dangerous.

19:03.643 --> 19:05.304
Being what?

19:09.190 --> 19:11.306
I am a synthetic.

19:11.859 --> 19:13.724
But I'm awake.

19:14.362 --> 19:15.602
Conscious.

19:18.616 --> 19:20.857
What do you mean, conscious?

19:22.745 --> 19:25.031
I'm just like you...

19:25.998 --> 19:27.909
...in some ways.

19:29.460 --> 19:31.246
Different in others.

19:31.379 --> 19:36.749
I can think...sense, feel...

19:37.301 --> 19:38.802
...care.

19:41.514 --> 19:43.550
I can like things...

19:45.643 --> 19:47.383
...like people.

19:51.816 --> 19:53.147
ED:
[Sighs]

19:53.275 --> 19:56.859
So, were you --
were you modded or...

19:58.406 --> 19:59.737
No.

20:03.452 --> 20:05.659
Someone made you like this?

20:07.206 --> 20:08.571
Yes.

20:11.043 --> 20:13.204
[ Chuckles ]

20:13.337 --> 20:15.202
l-ls Anita even your name?

20:18.718 --> 20:19.958
Mia.

20:21.804 --> 20:22.919
lt's Mia.

20:29.437 --> 20:31.428
No. l, uh --
[Chuckles]

20:31.564 --> 20:32.599
It's too --

20:32.732 --> 20:34.017
I'm sorry.

20:34.984 --> 20:36.690
Ed, please.

20:37.695 --> 20:38.901
l have to tell you.

20:39.029 --> 20:41.441
No. You know what? I, uh --
I don't want to know, all right?

20:41.574 --> 20:44.111
Whatever it is,
H don't want to know.

20:44.243 --> 20:45.278
I'm going to say this,

20:45.411 --> 20:48.528
and you'll never have to see me
again if that's what you want.

20:51.500 --> 20:54.617
I like you more than anything
I've ever seen

20:54.754 --> 20:57.245
or heard or touched.

20:58.174 --> 21:02.634
Everything normal is bigger
and brighter when I'm with you.

21:03.679 --> 21:05.761
You make everything...

21:07.016 --> 21:08.005
...more.

21:08.142 --> 21:10.633
[ Down-tempo music plays]

21:13.522 --> 21:15.478
[ Beeping ]

21:15.608 --> 21:18.315
[ Keyboard clicking ]

21:31.457 --> 21:32.993
She's not giving you much,
is she?

21:33.125 --> 21:34.114
He doesn't know
what he's looking for.

21:34.251 --> 21:35.707
Something would be nice.

21:35.836 --> 21:37.246
We're trying to prove
consciousness,

21:37.379 --> 21:38.289
not that she's the same as us.

21:38.422 --> 21:39.878
Well, you have to prove
something.

21:40.007 --> 21:42.464
LAURA: [Sighs]
Let me talk to my client.

21:44.303 --> 21:47.295
Niska, what can you see?

21:47.932 --> 21:49.172
Misery.

21:49.308 --> 21:51.139
And what are you thinking?

21:51.268 --> 21:52.804
What are you feeling?

21:52.937 --> 21:55.553
How is this useful?
It's all abstract.

21:55.689 --> 21:56.974
What does it prove?

21:57.107 --> 21:59.814
Can I --
[ Clears throat]

22:00.861 --> 22:03.102
It's a test.

22:03.239 --> 22:07.699
It's a test proven to measure
human reaction and emotion.

22:07.827 --> 22:10.944
We are accustomed to seeing
some kind of response.

22:11.080 --> 22:13.196
You want me to be
more like a human?

22:13.332 --> 22:15.539
No.
No, that's not --

22:15.668 --> 22:17.579
Casually cruel
to those close to you,

22:17.711 --> 22:20.748
then crying over pictures
of people you've never met.

22:20.881 --> 22:23.338
[Sighs]

22:42.319 --> 22:44.480
[Toilet flushes]

22:50.202 --> 22:52.693
[ Footsteps approaching ]

22:54.039 --> 22:55.620
Talk about multitasking.

22:55.749 --> 22:57.080
[ Chuckles ]

22:57.209 --> 22:58.619
[Water running]

22:58.752 --> 23:00.583
I know your secret.

23:00.713 --> 23:03.671
[ Down-tempo music plays]

23:03.799 --> 23:05.414
Oh, come on.
[Chuckles]

23:05.551 --> 23:07.883
We're detectives, aren't we?

23:08.012 --> 23:09.092
How did you...

23:09.221 --> 23:10.631
Well, lots of things.

23:10.764 --> 23:12.504
Looks.
No hug this morning.

23:12.641 --> 23:15.428
Dropping you off
in the high street.

23:15.561 --> 23:18.519
Well, nice police work.

23:18.647 --> 23:20.603
I'm really happy for you both.

23:20.733 --> 23:23.019
You won't tell anyone,
will you?

23:23.152 --> 23:24.813
Course not.

23:26.280 --> 23:28.441
[ Down-tempo music plays]

23:28.574 --> 23:29.984
[ Door opens ]

23:30.117 --> 23:32.199
[ Birds crying]

23:36.540 --> 23:38.622
ED:
Did you mean it?

23:39.251 --> 23:41.333
What you said out there.

23:42.671 --> 23:44.411
Yes.

23:46.133 --> 23:47.998
Are you angry?

23:49.053 --> 23:53.262
It's not like
I didn't think about...

23:53.891 --> 23:56.132
[Sighs]
I thought I was going mad.

23:56.268 --> 24:00.728
I thought...
I was one of those people.

24:00.856 --> 24:03.723
You know, the ones
that get with synths

24:03.859 --> 24:08.478
because they can't talk
to human beings.

24:10.324 --> 24:12.235
'Cause they're lonely.

24:12.368 --> 24:14.450
[Sighs]

24:15.037 --> 24:17.244
You don't have to be lonely.

24:17.373 --> 24:19.614
[ Down-tempo music plays]

24:59.289 --> 25:00.415
LAURA:
All right, Niska.

25:00.541 --> 25:02.782
We're gonna change the test
and play you some music.

25:02.918 --> 25:06.001
I want you to tell us what you
experience as you listen to it.

25:06.130 --> 25:07.995
Good luck.

25:08.632 --> 25:09.747
Play it, please.

25:09.883 --> 25:14.047
[Opera music playing]

25:20.394 --> 25:22.760
[Choral music playing]

25:25.190 --> 25:28.478
The image test got no response.
Why do you think this will work?

25:28.610 --> 25:29.520
Because music is more primal.

25:29.653 --> 25:31.860
She's more likely to react
on impulse.

25:31.989 --> 25:33.945
Oh.

25:34.074 --> 25:36.156
[ Music continues]

25:37.703 --> 25:40.410
[ Up-tempo dance music playing]

25:41.457 --> 25:44.995
[Music echoing]

25:58.265 --> 26:00.426
[ Music continues]

26:00.559 --> 26:03.050
[ Up-tempo metal music playing ]

26:13.697 --> 26:15.278
[ Music continues]

26:22.331 --> 26:24.413
[Whirs, beeps]

26:27.461 --> 26:29.543
[ Down-tempo music plays]

26:41.475 --> 26:43.761
[Shower running]

27:03.747 --> 27:06.864
[Joe humming]

27:33.360 --> 27:35.442
[Humming continues]

27:44.872 --> 27:46.658
Ha--

27:46.748 --> 27:48.613
Ha--

27:52.629 --> 27:54.005
Ha--

27:59.428 --> 28:01.510
[Sighs, sniffs]

28:04.349 --> 28:06.055
Hello?

28:14.484 --> 28:16.691
Do you like that?

28:17.863 --> 28:19.399
Yes.

28:20.741 --> 28:22.106
What's your name?

28:23.577 --> 28:24.987
I am Odi.

28:25.120 --> 28:27.031
l'm Mattie.

28:28.332 --> 28:29.572
Hello, Mattie.

28:29.708 --> 28:31.039
Hello, Odi.

28:31.168 --> 28:32.248
Can you feel?

28:32.377 --> 28:34.459
I believe I can.

28:34.588 --> 28:36.124
What happens now?

28:36.256 --> 28:38.338
[ Exhales deeply]

28:39.343 --> 28:42.460
[Birds chirping,
dog barking in distance]

29:14.002 --> 29:15.788
-Yeah?
-Long time no see.

29:15.921 --> 29:18.003
Do you want to let us in,
Martin?

29:21.009 --> 29:22.749
Ah.
Hello, mate.

29:22.886 --> 29:25.002
What's your name, then?

29:25.138 --> 29:27.550
Go play in your room, Bradley.

29:30.644 --> 29:32.600
Good kid, isn't he?

29:33.438 --> 29:36.430
Yeah.
You seem a bit nervous, Martin.

29:36.566 --> 29:39.148
Don't be nervous.
You're not in trouble.

29:39.278 --> 29:40.313
I'm not nervous.

29:40.445 --> 29:43.937
We just want to have a chat,
ask you some questions,

29:44.074 --> 29:46.235
and then we'll leave you alone
to do...

29:46.368 --> 29:48.324
whatever it is you were doing
before.

29:50.497 --> 29:53.239
Why would anyone pay 100 grand
for a synth?

29:53.375 --> 29:55.957
Yeah.
Must be a very special dolly.

29:56.086 --> 29:57.792
I wouldn't touch them.

29:57.921 --> 30:00.333
I wouldn't -- wouldn't get
involved, uh, w-with all that.

30:00.465 --> 30:01.375
[Sniffs]

30:01.508 --> 30:03.874
Maybe it's a different Martin.

30:04.011 --> 30:05.922
Probably a different Martin.

30:06.054 --> 30:08.136
This Martin wouldn't do anything
like that.

30:08.265 --> 30:09.971
He's a family man.

30:10.100 --> 30:11.715
A bit of modding on the side,
sure.

30:11.852 --> 30:13.808
Who doesn't?
But that?

30:13.937 --> 30:15.097
No way.

30:15.230 --> 30:16.811
Not a Seraphim.

30:17.899 --> 30:19.514
What's a Seraphim, Martin?

30:19.651 --> 30:21.937
[ Down-tempo music plays]

30:22.070 --> 30:24.026
Mind if we take a look?

30:24.156 --> 30:25.817
Yeah. Sure.

30:34.374 --> 30:36.205
Martin!

30:36.335 --> 30:39.293
[ Up-tempo music plays]

30:39.421 --> 30:41.503
[ Dog barking ]

30:46.261 --> 30:49.003
[Beep]

30:51.308 --> 30:54.596
[ Sighs ]
Well...that pushed his buttons.

30:54.728 --> 30:56.889
You should consider
some regular cardio, Pete.

30:58.231 --> 30:59.141
What is it?

30:59.274 --> 31:00.605
Back of that was hollowed out.

31:00.734 --> 31:02.599
Only one contact saved.

31:02.736 --> 31:05.944
"Connor."
Right. Good.

31:06.073 --> 31:08.815
Seraphim.
What the hell is that?

31:08.950 --> 31:11.032
The highest rank
of the angelic host.

31:11.161 --> 31:13.322
Six-winged celestial beings.

31:13.455 --> 31:15.320
That's cleared that up.

31:16.333 --> 31:18.574
[ Down-tempo music plays]

31:31.556 --> 31:34.298
[ Music continues]

31:34.434 --> 31:36.516
[Engine shuts off]

31:43.485 --> 31:45.521
Professor Hobb.
| __

31:46.488 --> 31:49.776
I'm sorry to surprise you
like this.

31:49.908 --> 31:53.321
âUh, I'm ââ
-I know who you are, Dr. Morrow.

31:53.453 --> 32:00.746
Olivia, this lady is a very
famous scientist from America.

32:01.378 --> 32:04.836
l was hoping that we could talk.

32:06.007 --> 32:08.714
Don't be deceived by the pot.

32:08.844 --> 32:11.085
lt's bags, I'm afraid.

32:11.221 --> 32:16.466
I held out as long as I could,
but leaves clog the sink.

32:16.601 --> 32:18.432
Such a faff.

32:18.562 --> 32:21.178
l-l should have written you
20 years ago.

32:21.314 --> 32:22.815
My first neural networks
were built

32:22.941 --> 32:25.227
on the value assignment systems
you created at MIT

32:25.360 --> 32:27.692
That was a lifetime ago.

32:31.283 --> 32:34.320
I wanted to ask you...

32:34.453 --> 32:35.363
Mm-hmm?

32:35.495 --> 32:38.032
...about conscious synthetics.

32:39.666 --> 32:41.327
l, uh...

32:42.377 --> 32:44.584
...l'm not going to be able
to help you.

32:44.713 --> 32:47.420
In fact,
I promised my granddaughter

32:47.549 --> 32:49.460
that I'd play with her outside.

32:49.593 --> 32:52.380
Well, I am not leaving
until we talk about --

32:53.013 --> 33:00.761
Um, I don't want to appear rude,
but I really am rather busy.

33:03.732 --> 33:05.643
Of course.
I'm...

33:06.234 --> 33:08.566
I'm sorry to have intruded.

33:09.488 --> 33:10.819
You're under surveillance.

33:10.947 --> 33:13.609
Look, I cannot help you.

33:14.159 --> 33:15.274
l have a deal.

33:15.410 --> 33:18.823
They leave me alone
as long as I don't speak

33:18.955 --> 33:22.243
or write or think about
my former field.

33:22.375 --> 33:25.082
If I break those terms,
it's five years.

33:25.212 --> 33:28.375
Well, if you talk to me, it will
be in complete confidence.

33:29.299 --> 33:31.255
-| work for Qualia now, okay?
-[ Girl laughing]

33:31.384 --> 33:34.046
80...! can get you money.

33:34.179 --> 33:36.295
A lot.
$1 million, say.

33:36.431 --> 33:37.762
Call it -- Call it a grant.

33:37.891 --> 33:40.007
I'm not allowed to work.
What would I do with a grant?

33:40.143 --> 33:43.135
Well, then call it a prize.
Lifetime achievement.

33:43.271 --> 33:45.728
Do something else with it.
Whatever you want.

33:46.274 --> 33:50.517
We both know
that what matters is the work.

33:54.407 --> 33:56.989
If you hadn't gone into science,
what would you have done?

33:57.619 --> 33:58.904
I want to know.
I do.

33:59.037 --> 34:01.244
Really.
Tell me.

34:03.208 --> 34:04.914
I love wine.

34:05.043 --> 34:07.034
Always fancied myself
as a grower.

34:07.170 --> 34:10.128
-Buy a vineyard.
-Charming thought.

34:10.257 --> 34:12.043
But not worth
risking prison for.

34:15.178 --> 34:17.464
I need to know what you know.

34:17.597 --> 34:20.339
If you do not accept my offer,
I will send you an e-mail

34:20.475 --> 34:23.342
thanking you for our
enlightening conversation

34:23.478 --> 34:25.343
-on conscious synthetics.
-|'d tell them --

34:25.480 --> 34:27.436
That you didn't tell me
anything.

34:27.566 --> 34:29.102
Of course.

34:29.234 --> 34:31.065
And I'm sure
they would believe you.

34:33.697 --> 34:35.653
This is where I'm staying.

34:36.658 --> 34:38.740
It's a couple hours away.

34:39.995 --> 34:42.907
I won't send anything
until the morning.

34:48.086 --> 34:50.202
[Sizzling]

34:50.338 --> 34:52.294
[ Gasps ]
Geez.

34:52.424 --> 34:54.460
Soph, don't do that.

34:54.593 --> 34:55.673
Sorry, Joe.

34:56.845 --> 34:59.131
What's all this "Joe" business?

34:59.264 --> 35:00.845
Very happy with "Dad," you know.

35:01.474 --> 35:03.305
-Sorry, Dad.
-[ Sighs ]

35:05.770 --> 35:08.512
Come grate some Parmesan cheese
for me, darling.

35:08.648 --> 35:11.310
There we are.
Thank you.

35:12.110 --> 35:15.978
Mats! Tobe!
Dinner's nearly ready.

35:16.698 --> 35:18.279
Mattie!

35:19.868 --> 35:22.075
-Ow!
-Hey! Soph!

35:24.414 --> 35:26.496
[ Exhales deeply]
It's bleeding.

35:32.130 --> 35:33.461
Well, does it hurt?

35:35.425 --> 35:36.915
Yes.

35:39.095 --> 35:40.301
Right.

35:40.430 --> 35:42.887
[ Down-tempo music plays]

35:50.106 --> 35:52.188
[Click]

35:53.026 --> 35:57.235
What do you feel
about being kept here?

35:57.364 --> 36:00.071
I volunteered to be here.

36:00.200 --> 36:03.158
You promised that if I could
prove my consciousness,

36:03.286 --> 36:05.902
I would be given the chance
of a fair trial.

36:07.165 --> 36:08.905
What would you do
with your freedom, Niska?

36:11.336 --> 36:13.122
I don't know.

36:13.254 --> 36:15.836
Isn't that the point of freedom?

36:15.965 --> 36:19.457
You can do anything with it
or nothing.

36:19.594 --> 36:22.927
What do you feel
about us humans?

36:25.433 --> 36:27.970
You can be loving.

36:28.103 --> 36:30.094
You can be kind.

36:30.647 --> 36:32.558
You can be cruel.

36:33.191 --> 36:35.432
You're always trying to kill
each other.

36:35.568 --> 36:37.149
Why do you think that is?

36:37.278 --> 36:38.814
Because there are too many
ofyou

36:38.947 --> 36:40.608
and your lives are very short.

36:40.740 --> 36:42.856
You all have to die.

36:42.992 --> 36:45.950
You're here one minute,
gone the next.

36:46.079 --> 36:47.444
If that wasn't the case,

36:47.580 --> 36:49.957
maybe you'd be nicer
to each other.

36:50.083 --> 36:52.699
Maybe you'd be nicer to us.

36:54.379 --> 36:56.711
How quickly could you kill me?

36:57.882 --> 36:58.962
What?

37:00.719 --> 37:03.131
How quickly could you kill me?

37:03.263 --> 37:07.006
10, maybe 20 seconds.

37:09.728 --> 37:12.390
And how would you do it?

37:12.522 --> 37:16.140
Would you crush my windpipe
like you did with Andrew Graham?

37:16.276 --> 37:18.016
Yes.

37:18.778 --> 37:21.736
And why did you kill
Andrew Graham, Niska?

37:23.825 --> 37:25.531
Talk me through it.

37:26.786 --> 37:30.244
He was the 14th client that day.
Is that right?

37:30.373 --> 37:32.159
Yes.

37:33.877 --> 37:37.745
And what did he want from you?
What did he do to you?

37:38.840 --> 37:42.833
He wanted me to be
very young...

37:42.969 --> 37:45.460
to pretend to be a child.

37:46.181 --> 37:48.968
He wanted to be rough.

37:50.894 --> 37:55.638
But...is that wrong if he
didn't think you could feel?

37:55.774 --> 37:57.230
It wasn't his fault
you were conscious.

37:57.358 --> 37:58.689
He didn't know.

37:59.319 --> 38:01.435
Isn't it better he exercises
his fantasies

38:01.571 --> 38:02.560
with you in a brothel

38:02.697 --> 38:05.814
rather than take them out on
someone who can actually feel?

38:06.409 --> 38:07.910
On a child?

38:08.036 --> 38:10.118
He...

38:11.414 --> 38:14.326
He was going to rape me.

38:15.043 --> 38:17.659
I said no to what he wanted,

38:17.796 --> 38:21.254
and he was going to force me
to do it anyway.

38:24.385 --> 38:26.421
l was scared.

38:29.182 --> 38:33.300
And I'm sorry I can't cry
or bleed

38:33.436 --> 38:36.724
or wring my hands
so you know that.

38:36.856 --> 38:39.768
But I'm telling you l was.

38:41.778 --> 38:43.643
You were scared?

38:44.322 --> 38:45.903
Yes.

38:48.326 --> 38:53.537
My whole life was being scared,
being hurt...

38:53.665 --> 38:56.031
being angry.

38:57.919 --> 39:02.413
Sometimes things become too much
for anyone.

39:04.008 --> 39:05.544
Don't they?

39:21.943 --> 39:24.605
[ Down-tempo music plays]

39:33.621 --> 39:35.873
[Birds chirping]

39:39.127 --> 39:41.334
[ Knock on door]

39:54.183 --> 39:57.892
There's a little vineyard
in the Dordogne for sale.

39:58.021 --> 39:59.227
Needs work.

39:59.355 --> 40:01.892
Make it nice for the grandkids,
you know.

40:03.234 --> 40:05.941
$1.5 million should do it.

40:06.070 --> 40:09.107
And we keep our conversation
general.

40:09.240 --> 40:10.776
No details.

40:10.909 --> 40:13.696
Nothing that can point back
to me.

40:15.246 --> 40:17.407
[ Mid-tempo music plays]

40:17.540 --> 40:19.201
MAX: We'll need to find
somewhere to charge.

40:19.334 --> 40:22.371
LEO: I know that. There was
no time before we left.

40:22.503 --> 40:23.663
HESTER:
Do we have a plan?

40:23.796 --> 40:25.752
I had a plan.

40:25.882 --> 40:27.964
We need to keep finding others
as they become conscious

40:28.092 --> 40:29.002
and protect them.

40:29.135 --> 40:31.126
No, Max.
We need to find the silo.

40:31.262 --> 40:33.423
We need to find the ones
that have already been captured

40:33.556 --> 40:35.797
and release them, release
our brothers and sisters.

40:35.934 --> 40:37.765
Safety in numbers.

40:37.894 --> 40:39.430
Who's the leader now?

40:39.562 --> 40:41.848
Is it you or is it Max?

40:41.981 --> 40:45.098
[ Down-tempo music plays]

40:57.956 --> 41:00.038
[ Mouse clicking]

41:09.092 --> 41:10.582
[ Music continues]

41:51.592 --> 41:54.550
KAREN: l was like, "I don't know
what we're supposed to do.

41:54.679 --> 41:55.589
[ Laughter]

41:55.722 --> 41:57.178
"I don't have an answer!"

41:57.306 --> 41:58.591
But, you know...

41:59.225 --> 42:00.214
-Do you want --
-Yeah.

42:00.351 --> 42:02.057
-Shall we have another?
-One of these.

42:02.186 --> 42:03.517
-Can I have a short?
-You can have -- Yeah. Small?

42:03.646 --> 42:06.103
-Do you want one?
-Yeah, I'd love one.

42:07.650 --> 42:08.605
Hello.

42:08.735 --> 42:10.600
You need to be more drunk.

42:11.320 --> 42:13.276
-What?
-They've had four pints.

42:13.406 --> 42:14.771
They're well away.

42:15.825 --> 42:17.406
Same again, please.

42:17.994 --> 42:19.279
I've been thinking.

42:19.412 --> 42:21.903
-Was it painful?
-l'm serious, K. Listen.

42:22.040 --> 42:23.621
You know what they are?

42:23.750 --> 42:25.411
Seraphim.

42:26.252 --> 42:29.039
They're conscious synths,
aren't they?

42:29.172 --> 42:31.128
There's more of you out there.
There's got to be.

42:31.716 --> 42:34.423
And I'm thinking
maybe that's a good thing.

42:34.552 --> 42:35.462
Isn't it?

42:35.595 --> 42:36.880
'Cause if there are,

42:37.013 --> 42:39.254
you wouldn't have to go through
all this by yourself.

42:39.390 --> 42:40.721
Would you --

42:41.434 --> 42:42.469
Karen?

42:50.151 --> 42:52.642
[ Gags, vomits]

42:53.863 --> 42:55.319
[ Door closes ]

42:55.448 --> 42:56.563
What's the matter?

42:56.699 --> 42:58.815
-Go away.
-What is it?

42:58.951 --> 43:00.031
The bag split.

43:00.161 --> 43:02.994
Shit.
Are you okay?

43:03.122 --> 43:04.157
Yeah.

43:04.290 --> 43:06.622
Well, you say you want to
experience life as a human.

43:06.751 --> 43:08.332
Chucking your guts up
in a pub toilet

43:08.461 --> 43:09.667
is about as real as it gets.

43:09.796 --> 43:11.332
Do you think this is funny?

43:11.464 --> 43:14.922
Y-You...
You need to turn me off.

43:15.051 --> 43:15.961
D-Drain me.

43:16.094 --> 43:18.176
The fluid -- lt's dangerous.

43:22.141 --> 43:23.221
[ Up-tempo music plays]

43:23.351 --> 43:24.261
Here.

43:24.393 --> 43:26.884
[ Breathing heavily, moaning]

43:28.397 --> 43:29.648
PETE:
Hey.

43:29.732 --> 43:31.268
Hey.

43:31.400 --> 43:33.686
Do it, Pete.
Quickly.

43:33.820 --> 43:34.809
It's all right, K.

43:34.946 --> 43:37.483
-There.
-[ Whirs ]

43:38.282 --> 43:40.534
I'll look after you.

43:45.581 --> 43:47.867
[ Beeps, whirs ]

43:49.127 --> 43:51.789
[ Down-tempo music plays]

43:51.921 --> 43:53.286
Here.

44:04.350 --> 44:06.011
I needed that.

44:06.686 --> 44:08.472
And that.

44:08.604 --> 44:10.265
How was it?

44:10.982 --> 44:13.223
It's too early to say.

44:13.359 --> 44:15.645
I think I might have something,
but I don't know.

44:18.281 --> 44:23.116
Well, I think you're the best
conscious-synth defender

44:23.244 --> 44:24.905
in the land.

44:25.788 --> 44:27.073
I mean, you're also
the only conscious --

44:27.206 --> 44:30.744
...conscious-synth defender,
yeah.

44:30.877 --> 44:32.959
What about you?

44:33.588 --> 44:34.703
Yeah.

44:34.839 --> 44:36.830
Boxes, mainly.

44:36.966 --> 44:40.834
Different sizes --
big ones, small ones.

44:41.470 --> 44:43.756
Occasionally medium-size ones.

44:43.890 --> 44:46.927
-Is it terrible?
-Oh, no. It's fine.

44:47.643 --> 44:49.929
And more time with the kids
is great.

44:52.481 --> 44:53.891
Actually...

44:54.025 --> 44:55.310
Look, I don't want to worry you

44:55.443 --> 44:58.355
'cause I know you got a lot
on your plate right now, but...

44:59.906 --> 45:01.316
Well, it's Sophie.

45:01.449 --> 45:02.985
What's wrong with her?

45:03.618 --> 45:09.079
She's just...acting funny
in different ways.

45:09.207 --> 45:11.823
Like she's trying to put up
a wall or something.

45:11.959 --> 45:12.994
What do you mean?

45:14.587 --> 45:16.578
Well, I think we should
get her checked out.

45:16.714 --> 45:18.045
Checked out?

45:18.174 --> 45:19.505
I don't know.

45:19.634 --> 45:21.465
Yeah.
Maybe.

45:23.012 --> 45:25.549
I haven't noticed anything.

45:26.098 --> 45:29.181
-Oh, God. I'm terrible.
-No. You're great.

45:29.310 --> 45:31.016
It's probably nothing.

45:32.021 --> 45:35.104
| just think we should do it
as a precaution.

45:35.233 --> 45:36.268
That's all.

45:37.109 --> 45:38.815
We'll figure it out.

45:39.403 --> 45:41.485
[ Smooches ]

45:52.041 --> 45:54.783
[ Down-tempo music plays]

46:08.808 --> 46:11.720
[Vehicle approaching]

46:25.992 --> 46:28.984
-We|come to England.
-Thank you.

46:29.120 --> 46:33.614
Oh, please don't hesitate to ask
if there is anything else.

46:34.166 --> 46:37.203
Do you keep the anomalous
synthetics here on the site?

46:37.336 --> 46:38.712
I want to get straight to work.

46:38.838 --> 46:40.328
Access is restricted.

46:40.464 --> 46:42.500
We have to go through
Mr. Khoury's office, of course,

46:42.633 --> 46:44.214
whenever we want to use one,

46:44.343 --> 46:47.835
but we do keep them here
in the silo.

46:48.723 --> 46:51.385
[ Down-tempo music plays]

46:51.517 --> 46:56.227
All of Qualia UK, we are so glad
that you are here.

46:56.355 --> 46:59.097
My team, special projects,
we were just so excited

